       <p>All Petroleum Engineering graduate students must take at least four out of the following Petroleum Engineering Core courses:</p> 
       <p>1. Mathematical Methods in Chemical Engineering (PETE 5355)<br>2. Thermodynamics (PETE 5020)<br>3.&nbsp;Transport Phenomenon&nbsp;(PETE 5010)<br>4. Fundamentals of Enhanced Oil Recovery (PETE 5310)<br>5. Flow Thru Porous Media (PETE 5060)<br>6. Reservoir Simulation (PETE 5300)</p> 
